=== Stock Chart Widget ===

{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.DisplayConfigurationWidget
| clazz = com.fluidops.iwb.widget.StockChartWidget
| type = 'DESCRIPTION'
}}
Go back to [[Help:Widgets | Widgets ]]

Stock Charts can be used when data is parameterized over time, e.g. to count the number of resources that were present in the database at a given point in time, and plot the outcome into a diagram that ranges over time. This chart type expects date information to be present in the format <nowiki><YYYY></nowiki>-<nowiki><MM></nowiki>-<nowiki><DD></nowiki>T<nowiki><HH></nowiki>:<nowiki><MM></nowiki>:<nowiki><SS></nowiki> (e.g., 2010-10-25T23:02:24 would be a valid date), so the argument provided in ''input'' must be given in this format. 

==== Configuration Settings ====

{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.DisplayConfigurationWidget
| clazz = com.fluidops.iwb.widget.StockChartWidget
}}

==== Example ====

<source>
{{
#widget: StockChart 
  | query = 'SELECT (SUM(<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer>(?grant)) AS ?sumGrant) ?start WHERE {
      ?role <http://research.data.gov.uk/def/project/grant> ?grant . 
      ?role <http://research.data.gov.uk/def/project/project> ?project . 
      ?project <http://purl.org/stuff/project/startDate> ?start . 
      ?role <http://research.data.gov.uk/def/project/region> ?region . }
    GROUP BY ?start'
  | settings = 'Settings:countdaily'
  | input = 'start'
  | output = {{'sumGrant'}}
}}
</source>

